<opener><dateline><date>16 July</date></dateline></opener>
<p>I have just got a very
<lb/>nice <hi rend="superscript">p</hi> letter which has
<lb/>cheered me up considerably
<lb/>also a letter from HP
<lb/>which I shall answer
<lb/>with great <unclear>discretion</unclear>. I 
<lb/>do not trust any one
<lb/> except <unclear>a</unclear> pv now after
<lb/>past experiences.</p>
<p>Feeling distinctly better
<lb/>after a walk this morning 
<lb/>&amp; another this afternoon
<lb/>to the RE, having tea
<lb/>with Col.<unclear>deVitroy</unclear>who
 <lb/>is revelling in his comfort
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6047" facs="#L1916_2297_img_6047"/>
        
        
           
            <lb/>able billet - a change 
<lb/>after what he has had.</p> 
<p>I am wondering what
<lb/>surprise there is in<del>f</del> store
<lb/>for me but trying not to
<lb/>worry unduly. Richardson
<lb/>came to <del>tea</del>  lunch a very pleasant
<lb/>interlude in the circumstances.
<lb/> If Comyn is out too we
<lb/>shall have a <foreign>tete a tete</foreign>
<lb/>at dinner.</p>
<closer><salute>Best <unclear>going</unclear></salute>
<salute>Your BW</salute>
<signed>WB Spender</signed></closer>
        
    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        
            
        

         

